After a week of stage 6 loadshedding, which sees up to four hours of no electricity, Eskom announced on Monday that load shedding would be reduced to stage three during this week. The Power Utility said stage four will be implemented on Monday afternoon and stage five would kick in from 4pm. Loadshedding would then be reduced to stage three at 5am until 4pm on both Tuesday and Wednesday, and stage four between 4pm and 5am on both days.  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here